THREE
people died and other two others were rushed to hospital after a head on crash,
on the R102 near Darnall on the KwaZulu-Natal. According
to IPSS Medical Rescue on arrival paramedics, found three occupants in one car
had sustained fatal injuries. IPSS
Medical Rescue spokesperson, Paul Herbst said an additional passenger from the
same car was in a critical condition. “Under the
care of advanced life support paramedics, KDM fire department used the jaws of
life to free the patient from the wreckage. The driver of the second car
sustained moderate injuries and was also transported to hospital by IPSS,” said
Herbst. The exact
cause of the high impact collision is unknown at this stage.   